<HEAD>
<TITLE>Nante</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY LINK="#FF2400" VLINK="#5080FF">
<P>These commands are in Twi.  When the Europeans came to Ghana and
began the vicious hunt for African slaves, they divided and conquered
neighboring tribes who had usually coexisted in peace.  Under these
conditions, the Fante and Asante, who speak languages from the Twi
family, fought with neighboring tribes and sold the vanquished as
slaves to the Europeans.  As the Asante and Fante dominated commerce,
their languages came to be spoken throughout the region.
<P>
Now that
Ghana is no longer a colony, each region falls more or less along
tribal lines.  Still, Twi is recognized as the dominant Ghanaian
language.  The Eve live in SouthEastern Ghana.  Many Eve who have never
left their region do not speak Twi.
<CENTER><BLINK><I><FONT SIZE=1>Who is speaking?  Who is being spoken to?
</FONT></I></BLINK></CENTER>
The images are "performed" magazine ads.  (None of the people in the
original ads were people of color.)  While the performers were held in
these poses they repeated the slogan of the ad - in English.  They
weren't allowed to change their position, or stop speaking until
commanded to do so. 
